    "transcript_preview": "# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 1\n\n62-HQ-83894 VOL 1 SERIAL 153 ONLY\n\n***\n\nFBI - CENTRAL RECORDS CENTER\n\nHQ - HEADQUARTERS\n\n| Class / Case # | Sub | Vol. | Serial # |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 0062 83894 | | 1 | 153 ONLY |\n\n8/11/1274168\n[Barcode]\nRRP003IXGA\n\n***\n\nDeclassification authority derived from FBI Automatic Declassification Guide, issued May 24, 2007.\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 2\n\nKNOXVILLE FILE #65-11\n\nRE: \"FLYING SAUCERS\" OBSERVED OVER OAK RIDGE AREA\nINTERNAL SECURITY - X\n\nENCLOSURES TO BUREAU:\n\nTwo photographs of reputedly \"flying saucers\"\nseen at Oak Ridge, Tennessee, during July 1947.\n\nPhotostatic copy of newspaper clipping appearing\nin the Knoxville News-Sentinel concerning these\n\"flying saucers.\"\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 3\n\nThis page is a mostly blank brown document cover containing the following markings at the bottom center:\n\n62-83894-153\nENCLOSURE\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 4\n\nKNOXVILLE NEWS-SENTINEL\nJULY 1947\n\n'FLYING SAUCER' PHOTOGRAPHED AT OAK RIDGE\n\nW. R. PRESLEY had snapped several pictures of his family and his house at 218 Illinois Avenue, Oak Ridge, the other afternoon and, noticing he had one film 'left on the roll, he turned and snapped it for a picture of the mountain.\n\n[Image: A photograph showing a landscape with a blurry object in the sky]\n\nHe had the roll developed, and look what he got on that last shot! Now don't start trying to explain it off. Just go ahead and say what it looks like. Sure. Sure. You're right. It is a Flying Saucer. A lot of folks have reported seeing the things. This, however, is the first time that one has ever been photographed over Oak Ridge.\n\nMr. Presley says this picture has all of Oak Ridge talking.\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 5\n\nPage 5 of 9\n\n[The page is mostly blank, containing only the following handwritten text at the bottom:]\n\n62-83894-153\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 6\n\nThis page contains only a photograph.\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 7\n\nThis page is blank, except for the following handwritten notation at the bottom right:\n\n62-83844-153\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 8\n\nThis page contains a black and white photograph of a residential area with houses, a utility pole, and a bright, circular object in the sky.\n\nThere is a handwritten \"2\" in the top left corner.\n\n--- Page Break ---\n\n# 65_HS1-834228961_62-HQ-83894_Serial_153 - Page 9\n\nThis page is mostly blank.\n\n[Handwritten at bottom right]: 62-83894-153"
